    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Does technically go against, but it is used quite commonly across projects. Would also be good to add a max spacing param, so that in the case of a really long param it would break to the next line:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\nuint256 i                                            = 0;\r\nuint256 foo                                          = 20;\r\nuint256 reallySuperLongVariableThatShouldBeOnNewLine = 50;\r\n```\r\n\r\nBecause I agree that the above looks kind of silly. Fmt should know that that's too long according to user config and do this:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\nuint256 i   = 0;\r\nuint256 foo = 20;\r\n\r\nuint256 reallySuperLongVariableThatShouldBeOnNewLine = 50;\r\n```",
